owl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles, who won the 60m at the New Balance Indoor Grand Prix in Boston earlier this month in a world-leading time of 6.44 seconds, aims to win his first 60m indoor national title against 60m world record holderChristian Coleman, who won last week's Millrose Games 60m in 6.51.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 733, \"end\": 743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"score\": 0.9982259282352919, \"rank\": 0.0017770203819868482, \"text\": \"Grand Prix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 0.8518113313806661, \"rank\": 0.16434642630821905, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}, {\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\", \"score\": 0.7855715336872432, \"rank\": 0.2690883397217461, \"text\": \"Coleman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coleman is undefeated against Lyles at the 60m distance; the two sprint stars last faced each other in the Prefontaine Classic 100m in September 2023, where Coleman edged the reigning 100m world champion, 9.83 to 9.85.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\", \"score\": 0.7855715336872432, \"rank\": 0.2690883397217461, \"text\": \"Coleman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\"}, {\"begin\": 990, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7570895094320592, \"rank\": 0.32084442150964343, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\", \"score\": 0.7855715336872432, \"rank\": 0.2690883397217461, \"text\": \"Coleman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Coleman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other notable U.S. stars expected to compete this weekend include 60m hurdles world record holder and reigning indoor world championGrant Holloway, reigning shot put Olympic and world champion and world record holderRyan Crouser, U.S. indoor mile record holderElle St. Pierre, U.S. mile and 3,000m record holderYared Nuguse, reigning Olympic and world pole vault championKatie Moon, 2016 Rio Olympic pole vault silver medalistSandi Morris, U.S. 60m record holderAleia Hobbs, andCole Hocker, fresh off of running the second-fastest two-mile in U.S. history at last week's Millrose Games (8:05.70).\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\", \"score\": 0.9999851704064001, \"rank\": 1.482339402636612e-05, \"text\": \"Holloway\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q40357\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\"}, {\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 0.9999998896789809, \"rank\": 1.0741547475124808e-07, \"text\": \"Moon\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M