ded that those athletes have met the World Athletics entry standardorhave a high enough world ranking within the qualification window.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 2142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1988, \"end\": 2001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9959513466664828, \"rank\": 0.002374705788641457, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2045, \"end\": 2060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999785043203, \"rank\": 2.1495578637050353e-08, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes can also earn a spot at the World Indoor Championships by virtue of winning the 2023 or 2024 World Indoor Tour for that respective event.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC Sports'Paul Swangardwill call the event, joined by four-time Olympic medalistAto Boldon, 2012 London Olympic decathlon silver medalistTrey Hardee, and two-time OlympianKara Goucher.Lewis Johnsonwill serve as reporter.\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9965315829752426, \"rank\": 0.0034798283936485173, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2376, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Boldons\", \"score\": 0.9999999963004029, \"rank\": 3.699572778769814e-09, \"text\": \"Boldon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Boldons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Boldons\"}, {\"begin\": 2384, \